git notes

#.gitignore

create a global gitignore
that is valid for all repostories but only for your user 

git config --global core.excludesfile=/home/peterl/.gitignore       ##<filepath>
global .gitignore
*.orig
Should you ever need them they can be reconstructed.

#merge
.orig are created when merge conflicts exist.
They remain even after a merge. You can delete them 
or prevent git from creating them in the first place.
Sh

git config --global mergetool.keepBackup false

git branch -a
gives remote and local branches


git line feed linux windows

Change the author of the last commit
git commit --amend --author="Author Name <email@address.com>"